In[4]:
def ela_image(path, quality=90):
    temp_filename = 'temp_file_name.jpg'
    ela_filename = 'temp_ela.png' 
    image = Image.open(path).convert('RGB')
    image.save(temp_filename, 'JPEG', quality = quality)
    temp_image = Image.open(temp_filename)
    ela_image = ImageChops.difference(image, temp_image)
    extrema = ela_image.getextrema()
    max_diff = max([ex[1] for ex in extrema])
    if max_diff == 0:
        max_diff = 1
    scale = 255.0 / max_diff 
    ela_image = ImageEnhance.Brightness(ela_image).enhance(scale)  
    return ela_image

def preprocessing(image_path):
    return np.array(ela_image(image_path).resize(image_size)).flatten()/255

In[23]:
def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, classes,
                          normalize=False,
                          title='Confusion matrix',
                          cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
   
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(classes))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, classes, rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, classes)

    if normalize:
        cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]

    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]), range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j, i, cm[i, j],
                 horizontalalignment="center",
                 color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')
def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, classes,
                          normalize=False,
                          title='Confusion matrix',
                          cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
  
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(classes))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, classes, rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, classes)

    if normalize:
        cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]

    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]), range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j, i, cm[i, j],
                 horizontalalignment="center",
                 color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')
In[64]:
ML_Model = []
accuracy = []
precision = []
recall = []
f1score = []

#function to call for storing the results
def storeResults(model, a,b,c,d):
    ML_Model.append(model)
    accuracy.append(round(a, 3))
    precision.append(round(b, 3))
    recall.append(round(c, 3))
    f1score.append(round(d, 3))

CNN

In[29]:
def CNN():
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Conv2D(filters=128,kernel_size=(5,5),activation='relu',input_shape=(128,128,3)))
    model.add(AveragePooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
    model.add(Conv2D(filters=256,kernel_size=(5,5),activation='relu'))
    model.add(AveragePooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(units=64,activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(units=16,activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dense(units=2,activation='softmax'))
    return model

In[65]:
CTS = load_model('models/cnn.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('CNN',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

In[66]:
CTS = load_model('models/inception.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('VGG19',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

In[69]:
CTS = load_model('models/dense.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('DenseNet',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

In[70]:
CTS = load_model('models/mobile.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('MobileNetV2',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

In[32]:
base_model = ResNet50(input_shape = (128,128,3), weights='imagenet', include_top=False)

x1= Flatten()(base_model.output)
prediction1 = Dense(2, activation='softmax')(x1)
model7 = Model(inputs = base_model.inputs, outputs = prediction1)
model7.summary()
model7.compile(optimizer = optimizer, loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])

In[71]:
CTS = load_model('models/resnet50.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('ResNet50',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

model8 = Model(inputs = base_model.inputs, outputs = prediction1)

In[72]:
CTS = load_model('models/resnet101.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('ResNet101',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

In[73]:
CTS = load_model('models/resnet152.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('ResNet152',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

In[74]:
CTS = load_model('models/xception.h5', compile=False)

Y_pred = CTS.predict(X_val)
Y_pred_classes = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_classes) 
plot_confusion_matrix(confusion_mtx, classes = range(2))

dl_acc = accuracy_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_prec = precision_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_rec = recall_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)
dl_f1 = f1_score(Y_true, Y_pred_classes)

storeResults('Xception',dl_acc,dl_prec,dl_rec,dl_f1)

base_model = NASNetMobile(input_shape = (128,128,3), weights='imagenet', include_top=False)

x1= Flatten()(base_model.output)
prediction1 = Dense(2, activation='softmax')(x1)
model11 = Model(inputs = base_model.inputs, outputs = prediction1)
model11.summary()
model11.compile(optimizer = optimizer, loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = ['accuracy'])

In[24]:
from tensorflow.keras.models import load_model
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Average, Input
import efficientnet.keras
In[25]:
def ensemble():

    model_1 = load_model('models/xception.h5', compile=False)
    model_1 = Model(inputs = model_1.inputs, outputs = model_1.outputs, name = 'Xception')

    model_2 = load_model('models/nasnet.h5', compile=False)
    model_2 = Model(inputs = model_2.inputs, outputs = model_2.outputs, name = 'NASNetMobile')
    
    models = [model_1, model_2]


    models_input = Input(shape =(128,128,3))
    models_output = [model(models_input) for model in models]
    
    ensemble_output = Average()(models_output)

    simple_average = Model(inputs = models_input, outputs = ensemble_output, name = 'Ensemble')

    return simple_average
In[27]:
ext = ensemble()
ext.compile(optimizer='sgd', 
              loss = 'binary_crossentropy', 
              metrics=["accuracy"])
ext.summary()
